Class ProductTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.GenericTree<IProduct>
      • tree.ProductTree
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ITree<IProduct>, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<IProduct>>

    public class ProductTree
extends GenericTree<IProduct>
    This class represents a ITree of IProducts. It extends the GenericTree and binds its typeparameter TREETYPE to IProduct. This means that there are only ITreeNodes of IProducts in the ProductTree.
    Author:
    OOP

      • deepCopy

        public ProductTree deepCopy()
        Description copied from class: GenericTree
        Creates a copy of the GenericTree and all its attributes and returns it. All attributes that implement the IDeepCopy interface have to be copied via the IDeepCopy.deepCopy() method as well.

        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 

         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
